# No System Commands

When working in this repo, only run commands that are directly required for this project.

## NEVER Run

- System administration commands: `reboot`, `shutdown`, `systemctl`, `service`, `init`
- Process killers on arbitrary processes: `pkill`, `killall`, `kill` (unless user explicitly says which PID/process)
- User/permission management: `chmod`, `chown`, `useradd`, `passwd`, etc.
- Network configuration: `ifconfig`, `ip link`, `iptables`, `ufw`, etc.
- Package management: `apt`, `apt-get`, `pip`, `npm install` (unless explicitly needed for project build)
- Disk/filesystem operations: `mkfs`, `mount`, `umount`, `fdisk`, `dd`
- Cron/scheduler: `crontab`, `at`
- Any command not directly needed to build, test, or read this project

## ONLY Run Commands That Are

- Reading project files (`ls`, `cat` equivalents via tools)
- Building the project (`make`, `gcc` as defined in project Makefile)
- Running project binaries (`./bin/bet`) **after user approval**
- Project-specific tools (`verus -chain=chips` RPC queries) **after user approval**
- Tmux session management **when explicitly requested by user**

## When in Doubt

Do not run the command. Ask the user first.
